summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingClinique Quickliner For Eyes is a long-wearing eyeliner that swivels up, glides on.
details: DetailsBenefitsSilky formula glides on.Stays on all day.Never needs sharpening."Smoke" with the smudge tip on the opposite end.Dermatologist and ophthalmologist tested.Allergy tested.Formulated WithoutParabensPhthalatesFragranceItem 2153501How To UseSwivel eyeliner up only 1/8-inch (pencil doesn't automatically retract, and too much exposure to air can dry it out.) Line eyes. Use smudging tool on opposite end to get desired effect. Allow color to set for 60 seconds to ensure transfer-resistance. Recap securely to protect from drying out.Remove with Take The Day Off Makeup Remover For Lids, Lashes & Lips.IngredientsCyclopentasiloxane, Synthetic Beeswax, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Arachidyl Behenate, Microcrystalline Wax / Cera Microcristallina / Cire Microcristalline, BHT.May Contain: Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Mica, Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Chromium Hydroxide Green (CI 77289), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Manganese Violet (CI 77742), Chromium Oxide Greens (CI 77288), Carmine (CI 75470), Aluminum Powder (CI 77000), Ultramarines (CI 77007), Ferric Ferrocyanide (CI 77510).Please be aware that ingredient lists may change or vary from time to time. Please refer to the ingredient list on the product package you receive for the most up to date list of ingredients.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Swivel eyeliner up only 1/8-inch (pencil doesn't automatically retract, and too much exposure to air can dry it out.) Line eyes. Use smudging tool on opposite end to get desired effect. Allow color to set for 60 seconds to ensure transfer-resistance. Recap securely to protect from drying out.Remove with Take The Day Off Makeup Remover For Lids, Lashes & Lips.
ingredients: Microcrystalline Wax / Cera Microcristallina / Cire Microcristalline

I will buy again for sure
media.caption: Me at 70.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I've been using Clinique products for many years, and the Quickliner for Eyes (not the Quickliner Intense) is only pencil eyeliner I can use. I have very sensitive skin and this is the only one that doesn't make my eyes water and itch. It goes on smoothly, lasts all day, and comes off easily with eye makeup remover.

Over time, I have tried most of the shades, but my favorite, by far, was Color 12 MOSS. It was a wonderful shade of green, not too dark or too bright. It really made my green eyes pop! I was very disappointed when it was discontinued. (Why was it?) I haven't been able to find another shade like it, that I can wear.

Although I will continue to use the other colors, I really miss MOSS! Please bring MOSS back!
faceoff_positive.headline: Love this eyeliner, but miss MOSS!

faceoff_negative.comments: I've been using this eyeliner for years with no problems. Now, within the past year or so, it will break off with very little pressure, sometimes before you hardly get it to your eye, and you end up with hardly any product left after a very short period of time. These liners being sold are either old and have been on the shelf a long time, the formula is drying out or changing in transit, or the formula has just completely changed. I know how to use it and have had absolutely no problems for many many years. I noticed some added "how to use" advice on here that I've never seen before, so my speculation is I am not the only one that has had this issue and rather than fix the problem, the blame is being put on the consumer and how they use it. That is just NOT the case. I used this for too long with no problems. CLINIQUE, PLEASE FIX THIS PROBLEM. This has always been my main eyeliner for years and would really like to continue using it.
faceoff_negative.headline: Has the formula changed?
